# Privacy Policy for BillSnapr

**Last updated:** February 16, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how logicbase ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and discloses your information when you use the BillSnapr mobile application (the "App").

By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

## 1. Information We Collect

We may collect the following types of information:

### A. Personal Information
We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us, such as:
- **Account Information:** If you create an account, we may collect your name, email address, password, and business details.
- **Transaction Data:** Information related to your sales, inventory, and customers that you input into the App.
- **Payment Information:** We do not store your credit card information directly. Payments and subscriptions are processed by third-party payment processors (e.g., Apple App Store, Google Play Store, RevenueCat).

### B. Device and Usage Information
When you access the App, we may automatically collect specific details about your device, including:
- Device model and manufacturer
- Operating system version
- Unique device identifiers
- App crash logs and performance data

### C. Permissions and Sensitive Data
The App requires certain permissions to function correctly. We request access to:

- **Camera:**
    - **Purpose:** To scan barcodes/QR codes for products and to take photos of inventory items.
    - **Data Usage:** Images are processed locally or uploaded to our secure servers effectively to manage your inventory. We do not use your camera for any other purpose.

- **Photo Library / Storage:**
    - **Purpose:** To allow you to upload images of products or your business logo from your device's gallery.
    - **Data Usage:** Selected images are uploaded to store with your product data.

- **Bluetooth:**
    - **Purpose:** To connect to external hardware such as **Thermal Printers** for printing receipts.
    - **Data Usage:** We use Bluetooth solely to discover and communicate with paired printer devices. We do not use Bluetooth for location tracking.

- **Location Services (Android Only):**
    - **Purpose:** On certain versions of Android, access to "Fine Location" is required by the operating system to discover nearby Bluetooth devices (printers).
    - **Data Usage:** **We do not collect, store, or share your GPS location.** This permission is strictly used to enable Bluetooth scanning functionality as mandated by the Android OS.

## 2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:
- **To Provide Service:** To provide, operate, and maintain the BillSnapr POS system.
- **To Improve the App:** To analyze usage patterns and fix bugs (e.g., via crash reporting).
- **To Process Transactions:** To facilitate billing and inventory management features.
- **To Communicate:** To send you service-related notices or promotional content (if opted in).

## 3. Data Storage and Security

- **Data Retention:** We retain your data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy or as required by law.
- **Security:** We allow industry-standard security measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.
- **Third-Party Services:** We use trusted third-party services for specific functions:
    - **Supabase:** For secure database hosting and user authentication.
    - **RevenueCat:** For managing app subscriptions and purchases.

## 4. Third-Party Links and Services

The App may utilize third-party services that collect information used to identify you. Please consult the privacy policies of these third-party service providers:
- [Expo](https://expo.dev/privacy)
- [Supabase](https://supabase.com/privacy)
- [RevenueCat](https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy)

## 5. Children's Privacy

The App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will delete it immediately.

## 6. Your Rights

Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data, including:
- Accessing your data
- Correcting or deleting your data
- Objecting to or restricting processing
- Data portability

To exercise these rights, please contact us at the email provided below.

## 7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

## 8. Contact Us

If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at:

**Email:** logicbase.platform@gmail.com
